LOCALSTORAGE:
👉️ "in local storage the value are stored as string"
 
 if somevalue = undefined; [in the localStorage]
 localStorage.getItem("somevalue") === undefined // false
 localStorage.getItem("somevalue") === "undefined" // true
 
 BUT if the key is not present in the localstorage then localStorage.getItem() will return 
 null[i.e the object not the string "null"]
 
👉️ ways to get item value:
▶️ localStorage.getItem("key") // returns value
 OR
▶️ localStorage["key"]		// returns value
 OR
▶️ localStorage.hasOwnProperty("key") // boolean
